<Link id="l01383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1383"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a7f2a3d4dcfee70225988aec53ff1e173">report&#95;fatal&#95;error</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;Don&#39;t know how to emit this value.&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1384"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1385"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We couldn&#39;t handle the requested integer size so we fallback by breaking</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1386"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the request down into several, smaller, integers.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1387"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Since sizes greater or equal to &quot;Size&quot; are invalid, we use the greatest</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1388"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// power of 2 that is less than &quot;Size&quot; as our largest piece of granularity.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1389"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> IsLittleEndian = MAI-&gt;isLittleEndian();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1390"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Emitted = 0; Emitted != <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a>;) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1391"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Remaining = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a> - Emitted;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1392"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The size of our partial emission must be a power of two less than</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1393"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Size.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1394"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> EmissionSize = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ae22967d11b695d268992470debfae4b2">llvm::bit&#95;floor</a>(std::min(Remaining, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a> - 1));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1395"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Calculate the byte offset of our partial emission taking into account</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1396"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the endianness of the target.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1397"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ByteOffset =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1398"><Highlight kind="normal">          IsLittleEndian ? Emitted : (Remaining - EmissionSize);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1399"><Highlight kind="normal">      uint64&#95;t ValueToEmit = IntValue &gt;&gt; (ByteOffset &#42; 8);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1400"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We truncate our partial emission to fit within the bounds of the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1401"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// emission domain.  This produces nicer output and silences potential</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1402"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// truncation warnings when round tripping through another assembler.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1403"><Highlight kind="normal">      uint64&#95;t Shift = 64 - EmissionSize &#42; 8;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1404"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(Shift &lt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">uint64&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">&gt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1405"><Highlight kind="normal">                         std::numeric&#95;limits&lt;unsigned long long&gt;::digits) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1406"><Highlight kind="normal">             </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;undefined behavior&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1407"><Highlight kind="normal">      ValueToEmit &amp;= ~0ULL &gt;&gt; Shift;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1408"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mcasmstreamer-cpp-/mcasmstreamer/#a11156cb1f872cbe35d40c6f36a21d56f">emitIntValue</a>(ValueToEmit, EmissionSize);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1409"><Highlight kind="normal">      Emitted += EmissionSize;</Highlight></CodeLine>
